## Competitor Analysis

### 1. Notion - The Modern Standard

**Website:** https://www.notion.so/

**Design Philosophy:** Block-based editing, flexible workspaces, all-in-one

**Typography:**
- **Primary Font:** Inter (Regular 400, Medium 500, Bold 700)
- **Why Inter:** Superior legibility at small sizes, consistent rendering, wide character spacing, tall x-height
- **Line Height:** Increased for readability, adjustable via `/toggle spacing`
- **Font Options:** Default (Inter), Serif, Mono (only 3 presets, no custom)

**Key Design Patterns:**
- **Block-Based Editor:** Every element is a block (paragraph, heading, list, embed)
- **Drag & Drop:** Reorder blocks freely
- **Slash Commands:** `/` opens command menu (headings, lists, embeds)
- **Nested Pages:** Infinite hierarchy
- **Database Views:** Table, Board, Calendar, Gallery, List, Timeline
- **Clean Iconography:** SVG icons, minimalist
- **Smooth Animations:** Block transforms, page transitions
- **Inline Comments:** Collaboration feature

**Pros:**
✅ Extremely flexible and powerful
✅ Professional, modern aesthetic
✅ Block-based = great for structured thinking
✅ Extensive features (databases, embeds, etc.)

**Cons:**
❌ Can feel overwhelming (too many options)
❌ Block-based = feels "fragmented" for linear writing
❌ Steep learning curve
❌ Overkill for simple notes

